# DreamWeaver MVP

DreamWeaver is an AI-powered mental wellness platform that utilizes natural language processing, machine learning, and cognitive behavioral therapy to provide personalized mental health support.

## Project Overview

This repository contains the Flask backend code for the DreamWeaver MVP. The platform offers API endpoints for mood tracking, personalized recommendations, and sentiment analysis.

## Installation

1. Clone the repository: `git clone https://github.com/your-username/dreamweaver-mvp.git`
2. Install dependencies: `pip install -r requirements.txt`
3. Download NLTK data: `python -m nltk.downloader vader_lexicon`

## Run Instructions

1. Run the Flask app: `python app.py`
2. Access the API endpoints using a tool like Postman or cURL

## API Endpoints

* `/mood`: Track user mood (POST)
* `/recommendations`: Get personalized recommendations (GET)
* `/sentiment`: Analyze sentiment of user input (POST)

## Future Development

* Integrate with AI-powered chatbots
* Develop a user-friendly frontend interface
* Implement subscription-based model and B2B partnerships
